                        ]
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Impact on the World",
            "subtitle": "Beyond Desktop Computers",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "kind": "bullets",
                    "items": [
                        "Used in servers and cloud infrastructure",
                        "Foundation of open-source education",
                        {
                            "text": "Influence on industry",
                            "subpoints": [
                                "Cloud providers",
                                "Research institutions",
                                "Government systems"
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Ethical and Social Impact",
            "subtitle": "Technology Serving Society",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "kind": "paragraph",
                    "text": "GNU and GNOME promote a vision where technology respects users rather than exploiting them. This approach influences debates on digital rights, privacy, and software ownership."
                },
                {
                    "kind": "bullets",
                    "items": [
                        "Encourages digital self-reliance",
                        "Reduces dependency on corporations",
                        "Supports global collaboration"
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "content",
            "title": "Conclusion",
            "subtitle": "Shaping a Freer Digital Future",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "kind": "paragraph",
                    "text": "GNU and GNOME are not just software projects; they are social movements embedded in technology. Their continued development shapes a world where users retain control, transparency is valued, and collaboration transcends borders."
                }
            ]
        }
